==Irish==
===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|[ˈagəs]}}
===Etymology===
[[Old Irish]] ''[[ocus]]'' "and", originally "proximity" < [[w:Proto-Celtic language|Proto-Celtic]] *''onkus-tus'' < *''onkus'' "near"

===Conjunction===
#[[and]]

----

==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
Old Irish [[acus]], [[ocus]]

===Conjunction===
'''agus'''

# [[and]]
#* aran agus ìm
#** bread and butter
# [[as]]
#* Tha e cheart cho math agus a bha e.
#** It is just as good as it was.

===Usage notes===
Agus is not only a copulative conjunction, but is also an emphatic copulative conjunction.
#* Nach truagh leat mi, agus mi am prìosan?
#** Do you not pity me, and I in prison?

